content.definition: The salary used to calculate expected and/or actual contributions.
content.name: Superannuation Fund Details Annual Salary For Contributions Amount

content.definition: The salary used to calculate a Defined Benefit members benefit entitlements.
content.name: Superannuation Fund Details Annual Salary For Benefits Amount

content.definition: Be 'At Work' on the first day of employment which is indicated by SuperannuationFundDetails.EmploymentStart.Date. 'At Work' means the employee is genuinely performing all the duties of their usual occupation or are not at work on that date due to some reason other than injury or illness.
content.guidance:
True = At work on employment start date.
False = Not at Work on employment start date.
content.name: Superannuation Fund Details At Work Indicator

content.definition: The hours of work which it is usual for an employee to work per week.
content.name: Superannuation Fund Details Weekly Hours Worked Number

content.definition: The Benefit Category may be used by your superannuation provider to determine product features applied to a membership or superannuation account.
content.name: Superannuation Fund Details Benefit Category Text

content.definition: The Date that the individual was registered with the Super Fund.
content.name: Superannuation Fund Details Fund Registration Date

content.definition: This indicator is used to communicate to the Fund that the member does not want the Super Fund to provide an Insurance product to them.
content.guidance:
True = Member does not want Insurance.
False = Member does want Insurance.
content.name: Superannuation Fund Details Insurance Opt Out Indicator

content.definition: The start date from which the Annual Salary for contributions determination is based.
content.name: Superannuation Fund Details Annual Salary For Contributions Effective Start Date

content.definition: The end date from which the Annual Salary for contributions determination is based.
content.name: Superannuation Fund Details Annual Salary For Contributions Effective End Date

content.definition: The date when a member's contributions commence.
content.name: Superannuation Fund Details Super Contribution Commence Date

content.definition: The date when a member's contributions cease.
content.name: Superannuation Fund Details Super Contribution Cease Date

content.definition: Description to accompany a change to a member's registration details.
content.name: Superannuation Fund Details Member Registration Amendment Reason Text

content.definition: Pay period start date that the contributions relate to.
content.name: Superannuation Contribution Pay Period Start Date

content.definition: Pay period end date that the contributions relate to.
content.name: Superannuation Contribution Pay Period End Date

content.definition: A contribution made by an individual for the benefit of a person less than 18, but not because they are the person's employer or where an employee directs an employer to make after-tax contributions for this purpose.
content.name: Superannuation Contribution Child Contributions Amount

content.definition: Contribution made by an employer for the benefit of an employee as mandated by an award or other industrial agreement.
content.name: Superannuation Contribution Employer Contributions Award Or Productivity Amount

content.definition: Employer contributions which are not mandated employer contributions
content.name: Superannuation Contribution Employer Contributions Voluntary Amount

content.definition: The salary used to calculate insurance amounts.
content.name: Superannuation Fund Details Annual Salary For Insurance Amount

content.definition: A short description to explain why the employee has ended their employment.
content.name: Superannuation Fund Details Employment End Reason Text

content.definition: Additional reportable information about the superannuation contribution.
content.name: Superannuation Contribution Other Details Text

content.definition: A description of the additional reportable information about the superannuation contribution.
content.name: Superannuation Contribution Other Details Description

content.definition: Indicates if entire balance of the member's contributions with the transferring fund is to be rolled over to the receiving fund.
content.name: Superannuation Rollover Transfer Whole Balance Indicator

content.definition: The rollover amount that the member is requesting the transferring fund to transfer to the nominated receiving fund.
content.name: Superannuation Rollover Requested Amount

content.definition: First day of the eligible service period in relation to the Rollover Transaction for the member.
content.name: Superannuation Fund Details Eligible Service Period Start Date

content.definition: The Preserved amount of the total amount being transferred.
content.name: Superannuation Rollover Benefit Components Preserved Amount

content.definition: The Restricted non-preserved amount in relation to the total amount being transferred.
content.name: Superannuation Rollover Benefit Components Restricted Amount

content.definition: The Unrestricted non-preserved amount in relation to the total amount being transferred.
content.name: Superannuation Rollover Benefit Components Unrestricted Amount

content.definition: The total sum insured amount of any death cover in place on the member account that will lapse as a result of the rollover transaction.
content.name: Superannuation Rollover Insured Death Cover Amount

content.definition: The total sum insured amount of any total and permanent disablement (TPD) cover in place on the member account that will lapse as a result of the rollover transaction.
content.name: Superannuation Rollover Insured Total Permanent Disablement Cover Amount

content.definition: The monthly sum insured amount of any income protection/salary continuance insurance cover in place on the member account that will lapse as a result of the rollover transaction.
content.name: Superannuation Rollover Insured Income Protection Monthly Cover Amount

content.definition: Indicates whether the member still holds an interest in the fund within the same account that the rollover has been paid from.
content.guidance: Would typically be set to "true" for partial rollovers and "false" for full rollovers but may have different treatment for funds who offer non-defined contribution accounts e.g. hybrid defined benefit/defined contribution accounts, risk-only superannuation policies etc.
content.name: Superannuation Rollover Remaining Benefit Indicator

content.definition: Indicates that the Tax File Number has not been provided.
content.name: Identifiers Tax File Number Not Provided Indicator

content.definition: The identifier is a superannuation fund generated employer ID.
content.guidance: A unique ID generated by a superannuation fund to an employer to identify the employer to the fund.
content.name: Identifiers Superannuation Fund Generated Employer Identifier

content.definition: The member has been assessed by the fund to have met the definition of a lost member - the member has either been uncontactable or their account has been inactive for a specific period of time.
content.guidance:
Uncontactable reported = Uncontactable - have been reported to the ATO.
Uncontactable flagged = Uncontactable - flagged within fund for reporting to the ATO.
Inactive reported = Inactive account - have been reported to the ATO.
Inactive flagged = Inactive account - flagged within the fund for reporting to the ATO.
content.name: Superannuation Fund Details Lost Member Code

content.definition: Describes the employment arrangement between the employee and employer.
content.name: Employer Conditions Employment Status Code

content.definition: Additional reportable information about a member registration.
content.name: Superannuation Fund Details Member Registration Other Details Text

content.definition: A description of the additional reportable information about a member registration.
content.name: Superannuation Fund Details Member Registration Other Details Description

content.definition: The start date for the additional reportable information about a member registration.
content.name: Superannuation Fund Details Member Registration Other Details Start Date

content.definition: The end date for the additional reportable information about a member registration.
content.name: Superannuation Fund Details Member Registration Other Details End Date

content.definition: This is the value, during the relevant period, of the KiwiSaver tax free component.  This amount is non-assessable and non-exempt income, that is tax free income.
content.guidance:
The KiwiSaver tax-free amount is the entire KiwiSaver amount made by a KiwiSaver scheme provider, but excludes any part of the contribution the KiwiSaver scheme or the member has previously shown to be:
- an Australian-sourced amount, which is generally an amount that was previously received by a KiwiSaver scheme from an Australian super provider and was originally accrued in an Australian complying super fund, or
- a returning New Zealand sourced amount - which is generally a New Zealand amount that has been previously treated as a non-assessable foreign fund amount in Australia.
content.name: Superannuation Rollover KiwiSaver Tax Free Component Amount

content.definition: This is the value, during the relevant period, of the KiwiSaver Preserved amount of the total amount being transferred.
content.guidance: A New Zealand-sourced amount in a complying superannuation fund is treated as preserved benefits in the same way as other amounts in the fund would be treated as preserved benefits.
content.name: Superannuation Rollover KiwiSaver Preserved Amount

content.definition: This is the unique reference number which identifies a payment.
content.guidance: This number is generated before the payment is made, and it is used in conjunction with other Payment Mechanism data items to enable a payment via a chosen mechanism type.
content.name: Payment Record Payment Reference Number

content.definition: The code that represents the reason for the payment of any Unclaimed Superannuation Money (USM) .
content.guidance:
Valid values are:
R = Temporary resident (received s20C Notice).
Q = Small lost member accounts (less than threshold and lost).
P = Insoluble lost member accounts (insoluble and lost).
A = Member reached eligible age.
N = Non-member spouse.
D = Deceased member.
content.name: Superannuation Rollover Unclaimed Superannuation Money Reason Code

content.definition: The date of the unclaimed money day, which is the last day of an unclaimed money period.
content.guidance:
The unclaimed money day provided must directly correspond to a scheduled statement day.
The unclaimed money days and scheduled statement days are:
30 June if the scheduled statement day is 31 October of the same year; or
31 December if the scheduled statement day is 30 April of the following year.
content.name: Superannuation Rollover Unclaimed Superannuation Money Date

content.definition: Additional reportable information about the superannuation rollover.
content.name: Superannuation Rollover Other Details Text

content.definition: A description of the additional reportable amount relevant to the superannuation rollover.
content.name: Superannuation Rollover Other Details Description

content.definition: An unclaimed super co-contribution transferred from co-contributions (CC) to Superannuation Holdings Accounts Special Account (SHAsa).
content.name: Superannuation Contribution Superannuation Holding Accounts Special Account Amount

content.definition: An unclaimed Superannuation Guarantee (SG) amount transferred from SG to Superannuation Holding Accounts (SHA), or pre 1 July 2004 employer super amount paid to the SHA.
content.name: Superannuation Contribution Superannuation Holding Accounts Special Account Taxable Amount

content.definition: An unclaimed Low Income Super Contribution (LISC) transferred from LISC to Superannuation Holding Accounts (SHA).
content.name: Superannuation Contribution Superannuation Holding Accounts Special Account Low Income Amount

content.definition: Additional reportable amount relevant to the superannuation contribution.
content.name: Superannuation Contribution Other Amount

content.definition: A description of the additional reportable amount relevant to the superannuation contribution.
content.name: Superannuation Contribution Other Description

content.definition: A unique reference number made of 18 digits, which identifies payments uniquely. It is referred to in bills, letters, reports to allow the correlation between the relevant report, bill or letter and the payment associated with it. It is generated before the payment is made, and it is used in conjunction with other Payment Mechanism data items to enable a payment via a chosen mechanism type.
content.name: Payment Mechanism Payment Reference Number Identifier

content.definition:
Salary sacrificing is a special arrangement between employers and employees where the pre-tax salary of an employee is sacrificed in return for employment related benefits. 
Salary sacrificed earnings from superannuation refers to the salary sacrificed earnings paid on behalf of employees.
content.name: Superannuation Contribution Employer Contributions Salary Sacrificed Amount

content.definition: This is the superannuation member's client ID which assists to uniquely identify the member for the provider.
content.name: Superannuation Fund Details Member Client Identifier

content.definition: The date the member commenced working with their last known main employer.
content.name: Superannuation Fund Details Employment Start Date

content.definition: The date the member finished working with the last known main employer.
content.name: Superannuation Fund Details Employment End Date
